title: Patricia Breen George Hitchcock Flower Girl in Holland Egg Ornament
description:
Ornament developed from George Hitchcock’s Flower Girl in Holland, 1887, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

This limited edition Patricia Breen ornament is inspired by George Hitchcock's (American, 1850-1913) painting Flower Girl in Holland.  Mouth blown and hand silvered glass, generously accented with Austrian crystals.  Crafted from the skillful hand of Patricia Breen in her Krakow studio, this design was produced in a limited quantity and made exclusively for the Art Institute of Chicago.

  • Dimensions: 3.34 x 2.16 diameter.
  • Materials: Glass, Austrian crystals.
  • Hand painted, silvered.
  • Made in Poland.
